author: David Greenwald | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Two brothers killed in Selma single-car crash
text:
Two brothers were pronounced dead on Friday night after a car crash in Selma, Oregon.
The single-vehicle crash was spotted at milepost 1.5 on Lakeshore Drive around 10 p.m. on Friday, according to the Oregon State Police.
Authorities' current evidence suggests driver James D. O'Grady II, 21, lost control of the car while heading west, and struck a tree on the east side of the road. Aaron J. O'Grady, 25, was his passenger. The two brothers were pronounced dead at the scene.
The two were driving a 2006 Chevy Cobalt.
